You are here: Cadiz, Inc. / Community 









Community
Tweet

Cadiz Inc. is named after Cadiz, California – a small Mojave Desert railroad outpost tucked along old historic Route-66.  We own nearly 35,000 contiguous acres in Cadiz (approximately 50 square miles) and have maintained a farming operation and a small community in this remote stretch of the desert, for over 25 years.  As a unique business in this area, we enjoy educating students and the public about our operations, water resources and the desert landscape. For a tour of our operations, please contact tours@cadizinc.com.
 




 
